The paper deals with optimizing predicate evaluation in databases, which is a core problem in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The problem formulation and analysis involve algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as well as complexity theory (cs.DC). The use of proofs and approximation algorithms suggests a focus on theoretical computer science (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's emphasis on optimizing query performance suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
